"There is a lengthy history of the emotional bonds that virtual communities build between users (Baym 2000; Rheingold 2000; Kendall 2002). Theresa Senft calls the set of obligations that people within connected networks have to each other tele-ethicality: ―a commitment to engage, rather than forestall action in our mediated communities, despite the potential for trickery and fraud."
